						               													<description>Mythic Coins Card Gameis a player vs player game where you control a mythic character such as a God, Goddess, or other powerful being.  Each character comes in their own Coin Deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Coin Deck contains a coin, display stand, dice, and 108 cards themed to that character.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is no shuffling or drawing cards. Players use the cards to build their character based on their vision of that character and strategy for the game.  A character can be customized to various power levels in the areas of Attack, Defense, Damage Bonus, Resistance, Health, Power, and Ability Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are over 50 unique Ability cards.  Players secretly choose a set number of Ability cards before the game. These are kept in a player's hand and only shown when used.  Most Ability cards require a specific amount of Power cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During a player's turn, they can choose to Activate a Character, Rest a Character, or Use a Card. Most cards result in a battle with another character. Some cards have other effects.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player must protect their Health cards and manage their Power cards while attacking and defending against an enemy.  Many attacks are resolved by opposing dice rolls. However, other attacks/defenses are countered by your opponent's cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is no board. The coin is placed on its display stand in front of the player.  The cards are placed next to the coin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is no limit to the number of players.  You can play in teams, a handicapped game, or other game modes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game balance is maintained since each deck has cards with the same abilities.  However, they are themed to fit the character.  An evasion defense may be called Flight for a Dragon but Teleportation for a Lich.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every card has a counter.  More powerful cards cost more to use.  You can only use an Ability card once.  These things prevent one or two cards from dominating the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When not playing, coins can be used as display pieces since they come with a stand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
